* module data filter specifications:
  P=pileup, O=overflow, U=underflow (add these as special histogram channels?)
  Histograms: array[A][D]++

  - MDPP (initialized to 16-bit output)
    * 16 amplitude values
      0001 XXXX PO00 AAAA DDDD DDDD DDDD DDDD

    * 16 time values
      0001 XXXX XX01 AAAA DDDD DDDD DDDD DDDD

    * 2 trigger time values
      0001 XXXX XX10 000A DDDD DDDD DDDD DDDD

    - MADC (initialized to 13-bit output, independent of resolution)
    * 32 amplitude values
      00XX X1XX 000A AAAA 0O0D DDDD DDDD DDDD

  Histogram properties:
    - name
    - size in bits
    - value/ channel
    - unit (Text: "ps") // Histogram may show at 64k: "24 ps/chan" or at 8k res: "192 ps/chan"
    - zero point        (chan 2048 is zero, left negative, right positive)
